    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-05T23:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-05T23:30:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/2253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Officer in Charge at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-06T11:00:00+06:30"
                            >May 6, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 6—8:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>324. Gandhi was released unconditionally at 8 p.m. today.</p>
                <p>A communiqué issued by the Government of India at midnight reads <hi
                        rend="italic">in toto</hi> as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In view of the medical reports of Mr. Gandhi’s health, Government has
                            decided to release him unconditionally. This decision has been taken
                            solely on medical grounds. The release takes place at 8 p.m. on May
                            6”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
